    "title": "Provider contract: external command protocol",
    "description": "Provenance REQ: jn7dcw8ce9gxw6v4p9p1k44jex83vgsn\n\nProvider is any CLI that accepts {role}/{ttl} template vars, outputs JSON {token, expires_at}, exits 0 on success. Provider config is TOML with [commands] section for mint/refresh/revoke.\n\nRules:\n- NS-009: Provider output contract — JSON with 'token' (required) and 'expires_at' (optional ISO 8601)\n- NS-033: Template variable injection prevention — argv array substitution, never shell; role validated alphanumeric+hyphens+underscores+dots\n- NS-034: Missing expires_at computed from requested TTL — now() + requested_ttl with warning\n- NS-035: Provider command execution timeout — default 30s, SIGTERM then SIGKILL after 5s, treat as exit 4\n- NS-036: Provider stdout size limit — reject output exceeding 1 MiB\n- NS-037: TTL format is integer seconds for providers — human durations are CLI concern only\n- NS-038: Revoke command receives token via env var — NOSCOPE_TOKEN, NOSCOPE_TOKEN_ID; exit 0 for already-revoked\n- NS-039: Refresh command receives token via env var — NOSCOPE_TOKEN, NOSCOPE_TOKEN_ID, NOSCOPE_TTL; same JSON output as mint\n- NS-040: Provider stderr handling — capture 4096 bytes on failure, discard on success unless --verbose, redact tokens\n- NS-041: Provider capability declaration — supports_refresh, supports_revoke booleans in config\n- NS-068: Provider command environment sandboxing — minimal env: PATH, HOME, LANG only\n\nProvenance stats: 2 resolutions, 11 rules",
