4. **NS-035**: Provider command execution timeout — default 30s, SIGTERM then SIGKILL after 5s, treat as exit 4
5. **NS-036**: Provider stdout size limit — reject output exceeding 1 MiB
6. **NS-037**: TTL format is integer seconds for providers — human durations are CLI concern only
7. **NS-038**: Revoke command receives token via env var — NOSCOPE_TOKEN, NOSCOPE_TOKEN_ID; exit 0 for already-revoked
8. **NS-039**: Refresh command receives token via env var — NOSCOPE_TOKEN, NOSCOPE_TOKEN_ID, NOSCOPE_TTL; same JSON output as mint
9. **NS-040**: Provider stderr handling — capture 4096 bytes on failure, discard on success unless --verbose, redact tokens
10. **NS-041**: Provider capability declaration — supports_refresh, supports_revoke booleans in config
11. **NS-068**: Provider command environment sandboxing — minimal env: PATH, HOME, LANG only
