## Summary: noscope-ydn — Provider contract: external command protocol

**New module**: `src/provider_exec.rs` (1,412 lines, 78 tests)

### Rules implemented (all 11):

| Rule | Function(s) | Tests |
|------|------------|-------|
| NS-009 | `parse_provider_output()` | 8 tests (valid JSON, missing token, empty token, non-string, optional expires_at, invalid ISO 8601, invalid JSON, extra fields) |
| NS-033 | `validate_role()`, `substitute_template_vars()` | 9 tests (valid chars, shell metacharacters, empty, spaces, slashes, argv substitution, no shell, multiple subs, non-ASCII) |
| NS-034 | `parse_provider_output()` (fallback path) | 3 tests (computed from TTL, warning flag, past expires_at) |
| NS-035 | `ExecConfig`, `ProviderExecError::Timeout` | 3 tests (default 30s, 5s grace, exit code 4) |
| NS-036 | `check_stdout_size_limit()`, `MAX_STDOUT_BYTES` | 5 tests (small, exactly 1 MiB, over 1 MiB, constant, zero) |
| NS-037 | `substitute_template_vars()` | 2 tests (integer seconds, no human suffix) |
| NS-038 | `build_revoke_env()`, `is_revoke_success()` | 4 tests (NOSCOPE_TOKEN, NOSCOPE_TOKEN_ID, no TTL, exit 0) |
| NS-039 | `build_refresh_env()` | 4 tests (all 3 vars, same output contract as mint) |
| NS-040 | `capture_stderr()`, `redact_stderr()`, `StderrPolicy` | 9 tests (limit, truncation, preserve short, redact tokens, discard/keep policy, UTF-8 boundary) |
| NS-041 | `ProviderCapabilities`, `parse_capabilities_from_toml()`, `validate_capabilities()` | 8 tests (defaults, parsing, consistency validation) |
| NS-068 | `build_sandboxed_env()` | 7 tests (only PATH/HOME/LANG, excludes others, exactly 3 keys, composition with credential vars) |

### Security measures:
- `ProviderOutput` implements `Drop` with `token.zeroize()` (NS-019)
- `redact_stderr()` replaces known tokens with `[redacted]` (NS-040)
- Role validation rejects all shell metacharacters (NS-033)
- Template substitution is pure string replacement, never shell (NS-033)
- Environment sandboxing strips all but PATH/HOME/LANG (NS-068)
